{"bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":1,"note":"<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901580\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909542\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909542\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; padding: 10px; margin: auto; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Management and Leadership<\/span><\/strong><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">Welcome to <strong>Module 1<\/strong> of MGT 200 Principles of Management! In this module, we will explore the fundamentals of management and leadership, covering topics such as the four main functions of management, the evolution of management thought, and the impact of love and culture on organizational strategy. The readings from <em>Contemporary Management<\/em> (Chapters 1 and 2) and <em>Love as a Business Strategy<\/em> (Chapters 1 and 2) will provide a solid foundation for understanding these key concepts.<\/p>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">As you progress through the module, consider how the principles of management and leadership apply to your own experiences, whether in work, school, or personal life. Reflect on the managers and leaders you have encountered and how their approaches align with the theories and concepts presented.<\/p>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><em>Need Support? Visit the <a title=\"Post your questions here\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78163\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78163\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Course Q&amp;A Discussion Board<\/a><\/em><\/p>\n    <hr \/>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><em>Time Commitment: Approximately 4 Hours<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901584\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909535\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909535\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Learning Objectives<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><strong>Through active engagement in this module, learners should be able to:<\/strong><\/p>\n    <ol class=\"list-decimal pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Summarize<\/strong> what it means to be a manager. (CLO 1, 2)<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Compare and contrast<\/strong> the four functions of management. (CLO 1, 2, 5)<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Illustrate<\/strong> 3 major theorists in the evolution of management thought. (CLO 3)<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Identify<\/strong> how love and culture impact strategy. (CLO 5)<\/li>\n    <\/ol>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901585\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909544\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909544\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Learning Materials&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><em>The following carefully curated materials are designed to help you solidly understand this module's key concepts and principles.<\/em><\/p>\n    <h4><strong>Reading(s)<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <ul>\n        <li><strong>Contemporary Management<\/strong><\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <ul>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <ul class=\"list-disc pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 1: Managers and Managing<\/li>\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 2: The Evolution of Management Thought<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/li>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <div style=\"padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n                <details>\n                    <summary style=\"cursor: pointer;\"><em>Chapter Summaries<\/em><\/summary>\n                    <div style=\"padding: 5px 15px;\">\n                        <p><strong>Contemporary Management<\/strong><\/p>\n                        <ul>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 1 Managers and Managing.<\/strong> Chapter 1 examines what management is, including what managers do and how they use resources to achieve organizational goals. The chapter highlights the four main functions of management (<em>planning, organizing, leading, and controlling<\/em>), exploring the levels of management (<em>first-line, middle, and top<\/em>), as well as the importance of three types of managerial skills (<em>conceptual, human, and technical<\/em>). The chapter concludes with a discussion of the major changes and challenges brought forth by <em>increased globalization and advancement in information technology<\/em> and competition faced by managers today.<\/li>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 2 The Evolution of Management Thought.<\/strong> In this chapter, how management thought has evolved in modern times and the central concerns that have guided ongoing advances in management theory are explored. First, the classical management theories that emerged around the turn of the twentieth century are examined. Next, behavioral management theories developed before and after World War II are examined, and then management science theory, which developed during the second World War. Finally, the theories developed to help explain how the external environment affects how organizations and managers operate are examined.<\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/details>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/li>\n        <li>\n            <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><strong>Love as a Business Strategy<\/strong><\/p>\n            <ul class=\"list-disc pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 1: What Is Love? (Baby Don't Hurt Me)<\/li>\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 2: Culture Eats Strategy for Breakfast<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/li>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <div style=\"padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n                <details>\n                    <summary style=\"cursor: pointer;\"><em>Chapter Summaries<\/em><\/summary>\n                    <div style=\"padding: 5px 15px;\">\n                        <p><strong>Love as a Business Strategy<\/strong><\/p>\n                        <ul>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 1. What Is Love? (Baby Don't Hurt Me).<\/strong> In November 2015, Softway had its darkest day. Confronted with an unexpected downturn and desperate to keep his company afloat, CEO Mohammad Anwar agreed to lay off over a third of Softway's workforce&mdash;around a hundred employees in all. This grim reality, coupled with the dehumanizing process of letting these team members go and the very real prospect that Mohammad might lose his company anyway, shook Mohammad to his core and led to a prolonged period of soul-searching. It was in this introspective-yet-brooding mood that Mohammad found himself at a University of Houston football game with his brother a few weeks after the massive layoffs at Softway. What he discovered at this game was that love does matter.<\/li>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 2. Culture Eats Strategy for Breakfast.<\/strong> To make a point on worker responsibility, Mohammad sent a toxic email to his employees that shook them to their core. Glassdoor reviews have stated, \"The upper management is completely unprofessional. Expect to be ridiculed, yelled at, or cursed. You can also look forward to petty emails about the condition of the refrigerator with demands that you meet to clean it (which you may not even use)... If you see any good reviews, you can assume they're written by HR!\" This was a difficult lesson Mohammad learned, that culture eats strategy for breakfast. He had a lot of change in front of him.<\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/details>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <h4><strong>Multimedia<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/youtu.be\/3sK3wJAxGfs?feature=shared\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Navy Seal Admiral - If You Want to Change the World, Make Your Bed<\/a> [6:00 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/simon_sinek_why_good_leaders_make_you_feel_safe?utm_campaign=tedspread&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=tedcomshare\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Why Good Leaders Make You Feel Safe<\/a> [11:46 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/stanley_mcchrystal_listen_learn_then_lead?utm_campaign=tedspread&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=tedcomshare\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Stanley McChrystal: Listen, Learn, Then Lead<\/a> [15:22 minutes]<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901586\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909539\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909539\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Tasks to Complete or Submit<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><em>Completing the following tasks and assignments is crucial for demonstrating your understanding, applying your knowledge, and engaging with your peers and instructor.<\/em><\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸ“š <\/span><strong>Engage with Course Content<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Read the assigned chapters from Contemporary Management and Love as a Business Strategy to build a strong foundation in management and leadership principles. Watch the provided videos on leadership and management to gain insights from real-world examples and expert perspectives.<\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸ§© <\/span><strong>Assess Your Understanding<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Complete the <a title=\"Week #1 Quiz (CM Chapters 1-2, LAABS Chapters 1-2)\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140559\" data-course-type=\"quizzes.next\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140559\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Module 1 Quiz <\/a>to test your knowledge of the key concepts and principles covered in this module. The quiz is designed to reinforce your learning and provide feedback on areas for improvement. <strong>Due:<\/strong><\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸ’¬ <\/span><strong>Participate in a Discussion or Attend a Zoom Session<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Contribute to the <a title=\"Module 1 Discussion Forum\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78162\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78162\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Module 1 Discussion<\/a> by sharing your thoughts, experiences, and questions about the course content. Engage with your classmates' posts to foster a collaborative learning environment. <strong>Due:<\/strong><span>&nbsp;<\/span><em>The initial post is due Thursday; the peer responses are due Sunday.<\/em><\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸš€ <\/span><strong>Apply Your Knowledge<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Start brainstorming ideas for the <a title=\"Course Spanning Project Part 1 - Leader Interview Presentation Draft\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140468\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140468\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Course Spanning Project Part 1<\/a>, which will allow you to apply the concepts and theories learned in this module to a real-world scenario. This project will be a key component of your learning journey and is due in Module 4. You may also read ahead to learn about the expectations for the <a title=\"Course Spanning Project Part 2 - Leader Interview Presentation Final\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140476\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140476\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Course Spanning Project Part 2.&nbsp;<\/a><\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\" style=\"display: flex; align-items: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; margin-right: 10px;\">ðŸŒŸ<\/span><strong>Begin Working on Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p><em>This is a team\/group assignment!<\/em><\/p>\n    <p>This week, you will be assigned to a <a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/community.canvaslms.com\/t5\/Student-Guide\/How-do-I-view-my-Canvas-groups-as-a-student\/ta-p\/281\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">team\/group<\/a> to begin working on the <a title=\"Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/142488\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/142488\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello<\/a> assignment. This team project is designed to help you apply the principles of management you've learned throughout the course to develop various aspects of an imaginary organization.<\/p>\n    <p>As you start working with your team, consider the following tips for effective online collaboration:<\/p>\n    <ul>\n        <li><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/community.canvaslms.com\/t5\/Student-Guide\/How-do-I-create-a-discussion-in-a-group-as-a-student\/ta-p\/350\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Introduce yourself<\/a> to your team members and share your strengths, weaknesses, and communication preferences.<\/li>\n        <li>Establish a regular <a class=\"inline_disabled\" title=\"Link\" href=\"https:\/\/community.canvaslms.com\/t5\/Student-Guide\/How-do-I-view-my-Canvas-groups-as-a-student\/ta-p\/281\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">meeting schedule or check-in <\/a>process to&nbsp;ensure everyone is on the same page.<\/li>\n        <li>Assign roles and responsibilities to each team member to promote accountability and efficiency.<\/li>\n        <li>Use the Trello board to organize tasks, set deadlines, and track progress.<\/li>\n        <li>Maintain open and respectful communication and address any conflicts or issues promptly.<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <p>The Trello assignment is due at the end of Module 6, so work consistently with your team to create a well-developed fictitious company.&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <hr \/>\n    <h4><span><strong>Engage with Your Instructor and Peers<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n    <p style=\"border-left: 4px solid #e45424; padding-left: 10px;\"><span><strong>Optional Zoom Session<\/strong>: During Modules 1, 3, and 6, you will have the option to join a LIVE Zoom discussion, which will replace this week's online discussion points if you attend. If you come prepared and participate fully in the Zoom discussion sessions, you will not be required to complete the Discussion Forum for this week, as this will replace it for you.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<hr \/>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f2f4f8; color: #374a67; padding: 25px; width: 100%;\">\n    <h2 style=\"background-color: #e45424; color: #4e606a; padding: 25px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"color: #141414;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Summary<\/span> <span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">of This Module's Learning Tasks<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n    <div class=\"two-col-panels\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-sm card bg-light\">\n                <ul>\n                    <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n                        <ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Monday<\/strong>: Engage with this Module's Content<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Wednesday<\/strong>: Complete Module 1 Quiz<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Thursday<\/strong>: Initial Discussion Post Due<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Sunday<\/strong>: Peer Response Due<\/span><\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/li>\n                <\/ul>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/div>\n    <\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Click on the Next button below to continue in this module.<\/em> â–¼<\/p>"}